<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Eye-ball" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Eye-ball,</orth> the globe or apple of the eye: <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.30" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.7.79" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 7, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.169" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 169</bibl>. == eye: <cit><quote>look in mine --s, there thy beauty lies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 119" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 119</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>rolling his greedy --s in his head,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 368" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 368</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>invisible to every e. else,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.303" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 303</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.369" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 369</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.5.47" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 5, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 1, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 104</bibl>.

